## Set up SCA with Stripe

You do not need to do anything because we set up 3DS2 on your service by default.

Stripe automatically applies SCA exemptions to transactions where appropriate.

## Set up SCA with Worldpay

Worldpay sends all transactions using 3DS2 or 3DS1. 3DS Flex is the Worldpay product that enables 3DS2 payment authentication. You must pay a fee to Worldpay to use 3DS Flex.

Worldpay sends you your 3DS Flex credentials when you [connect your live account to Worldpay](/switching_to_live/set_up_a_live_worldpay_account/#connect-your-live-account-to-worldpay).

Worldpay does not apply any SCA exemptions to transactions.

### Set up 3DS2 (3DS Flex)

1. In the [GOV.UK Pay admin tool](https://selfservice.payments.service.gov.uk/my-services), select the account you want to set up on the __My services__ page.
1. In __Settings__, make sure 3D Secure is set to __On__.
1. In __Your PSP__, enter your 3DS Flex credentials.
1. Select __Save credentials__.
1. Select __Turn on 3DS Flex__.

If you turn off 3DS Flex later, your account will use 3DS1 by default.

### Check 3DS1 is enabled

Worldpay enables 3DS1 on transactions by default. You can check if 3DS1 is enabled on your service.

1. Select the relevant account on the __My services__ page in the GOV.UK Pay admin tool.
1. In __Settings__, select the __View__ link under 3D Secure.
1. Check 3D Secure is set to __On__.

## Set up SCA with ePDQ

3DS2 is not available for ePDQ. You can only enable 3DS1.

## Set up SCA with Smartpay

3DS2 is not available for Smartpay. You can only enable 3DS1.

1. In the GOV.UK admin tool, select the account you want to set up on the __My services__ page
1. In __Settings__, select the __View__ link under 3D Secure.
1. Select __On__.

You do not need to do anything in your Smartpay account.

Smartpay does not apply any SCA exemptions to transactions.

## Further information

For more information on SCA including payment exemptions, [see the GOV.UK Pay page on SCA](https://www.payments.service.gov.uk/3d-secure-2/).
